<p><a name="top"></a></p>
<h1>ESSUM35950 - Requirements relating to share options - exercise rights: S409A US taxpayers</h1>
<p>Difficulties may arise for SAYE option holders if during the life of an option they are transferred to work in the U.S.A. and become subject to US Tax. It is therefore acceptable for the following provisions to be included in an approved SAYE scheme, amendments will also be approved to existing schemes to make similar provision. It will not be acceptable for there to be additional lapsing provisions in these circumstances.</p><a name="IDA41NQG"></a><h2>Within definitions</h2><br><table class="tableborder">
<tr>
<td><span class="pnopadding">“Taxable Year”</span></td>
<td><span class="pnopadding">the calendar year or, if it would result in a longer period for the exercise of an Option, the 12 month period in respect of which the Option holder’s employing company is obliged to pay tax</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span class="pnopadding">“US Tax”</span></td>
<td><span class="pnopadding">Taxation under the tax rules of the United States of America</span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><span class="pnopadding">“US Taxpayer”</span></td>
<td><span class="pnopadding">a person who is subject to US Tax</span></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><a href="#top" name="bottom">Top of page</a></p><a name="IDAV3NQG"></a><h2>Separate rule required as follows</h2>
<p>This rule shall apply to US Taxpayers. Notwithstanding anything contrary contained in this Plan, a US Taxpayer may only exercise an Option within the shorter of any exercise period specified in the rules of this Plan and the expiry of 2.5 calendar months after the end of the Taxable Year in which the Option first becomes exercisable.</p><br><div class="manual-nav">
